.SH NAME
refind-btrfs-snapshots-list-volumes - List all btrfs filesystems/volumes


.SH SYNOPSIS
\fBrefind-btrfs-snapshots list volumes [flags]\fP


.SH DESCRIPTION
List all btrfs filesystems/volumes detected on the system.

.PP
Shows device path, mount point, and the best available identifier for each volume.
The IDENTIFIER column shows the preferred identifier value, and TYPE shows what
kind of identifier it is (UUID, PARTUUID, LABEL, PARTLABEL, or DEVICE).


.SH OPTIONS
\fB-h\fP, \fB--help\fP[=false]
	help for volumes

.PP
\fB--json\fP[=false]
	Output in JSON format

.PP
\fB--show-all-ids\fP[=false]
	Show all device identifiers (UUID, PARTUUID, LABEL, etc.)


.SH OPTIONS INHERITED FROM PARENT COMMANDS
\fB--config\fP=""
	config file (default is /etc/refind-btrfs-snapshots.yaml)

.PP
\fB--local-time\fP[=false]
	Display times in local time instead of UTC

.PP
\fB--log-level\fP="info"
	log level (trace, debug, info, warn, error, fatal, panic)


